==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Republish
<hw>Re*pub"lish</hw> <pr>(r?-p?b"l?sh)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Republished</conjf>
<pr>(-l?sht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Republishing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To publish anew;
specifically, to publish in one country (a work first published in
another); also, to revive (a will) by reexecution or codicil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Subsecquent to the purchase or contract, the devisor
<qex>republished</qex> his will.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Republisher</ent>⟦br⟧
